## This commit (stage 2/10: call writes)
call_start/call_end implement ClickHouse calls_merged part-merge: an end
arriving before its start creates an end-only stub (_CallRec with
op_name/started_at None); a late start fills the stub; calls_query
excludes rows with op_name/started_at still None (incomplete merge rows
are invisible, as in CH where the start part supplies those columns).
calls_delete was rewritten from the project-wide parent walk (round 1,
SQLite-style) to ClickHouse semantics: RequestTooLarge over
MAX_DELETE_CALLS_COUNT (1000) requested ids, descendant discovery
trace-scoped (requested calls' trace_ids -> children map -> DFS), roots
always counted even if nonexistent, set-based count (no double counting).

## Errors & Mistakes
- A flaky ref-filter test exposed the missing part-merge: end-before-start
  parts were silently dropped. Fixed by the stub mechanism; verified with
  4 stable reruns.
- Round 1 calls_delete counted descendants + requested ids with
  duplicates (a requested id that is also a descendant of another
  requested id counted twice); CH uses one set.

